@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home";
}
@section scripts{
    <script src="~/Scripts/charting.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
    <script>
        function loadHomePageCharts() {
            loadTopSellersBarChart('topSellersByProduct', '/api/TopSellingProducts/');
            loadTopSellersPieChart('topSellersByCategory', '/api/TopSellingCategories/');
            loadMoversAndLosersBarChart('moversAndLosersChartContainer', '/api/MoversAndLosers/');
        }

        $(function () {            
            google.charts.setOnLoadCallback(loadHomePageCharts);
        })
    </script>
}

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">        
        Putting a price on items that are "no longa" available in stores can be extremely difficult. With such a wealth of information out there, it can be hard to get a clear idea of what an item is worth.<br/><br/>
        Here at NoLonga we're going to try and change that, we wanted to take sale price information and apply the same techniques to that as the Stock market so you can get a clear idea of price, trends and hopefully be able to time your sale or purchase to maximise your gains!
    </div>
</div>

